  heroImgPosition="50%"
  overviewTitle="The simplest investment in cavity prevention."
  overviewText="Fluoride works by remineralizing the early stages of enamel erosion — essentially reversing the initial damage before a cavity forms. When bacteria in the mouth produce acid from sugar, that acid demineralizes enamel. Fluoride draws calcium and phosphate back into the enamel structure, making it harder and more acid-resistant than it was before. In-office fluoride varnish delivers a concentration several times higher than any toothpaste or rinse, providing months of enhanced protection in a 2-minute application."
  overviewExtra="We apply fluoride varnish to patients of all ages at our Bayside practice — not just children. Adults with a history of cavities, patients with dry mouth (which accelerates decay), patients undergoing orthodontic treatment, and anyone consuming acidic beverages regularly can benefit significantly from twice-yearly fluoride application. Patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck who are proactive about preventing dental work rather than reacting to it often cite fluoride treatments as a small but consistent part of their prevention strategy. It takes two minutes and costs very little — the ROI compared to a single filling is dramatic."
