      a: 'Not at all. Adults at higher cavity risk — those with dry mouth, a history of frequent decay, acidic diets, or exposed root surfaces — benefit significantly from professional fluoride application.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How is in-office fluoride different from toothpaste?',
      a: 'In-office fluoride varnish contains a much higher concentration than any OTC product. It stays in contact with enamel for hours, delivering a deeper remineralizing effect.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How long does treatment take?',
      a: 'The application takes about 2–3 minutes. We ask that you avoid eating, drinking, or rinsing for 30 minutes afterward to allow the fluoride to fully absorb.',
